{"type":"message","id":"bb46a6c6","parentId":"4fef302e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:21:22.850Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"是全局吗\" (Is it global?) in response to my question about Sorftime MCP being a global setting or not. But I wasn't asking if something was global - I was asking what Sorftime MCP covers. Maybe they're asking if Sorftime MCP is a global MCP server (available to all agents) or if it needs to be configured per-agent.\n\nLet me re-read the context... The user mentioned \"sorftime mcp\" - I think they might be asking whether Sorftime MCP needs to be configured globally in OpenClaw, or they might be responding to my question about whether Sorftime MCP covers multiple platforms.\n\nActually, looking at the flow:\n\n\n1. User mentioned browser visualization collection tool running successfully\n2. I asked if we still need MCP\n3. User said they use SofaMCP (not Sorftime - maybe they mistyped or I misheard)\n4. User said SofaMCP already installed, key expired, will give new key tonight\n5. Then user said \"sorftime mcp\"\n6. I asked what Sorftime MCP covers\n7. User asks \"是全局吗\" - could mean \"Is it global?\" referring to Sorftime MCP's scope/availability\n\nI think the user is asking whether Sorftime MCP is a global/available tool, possibly related to the key they mentioned. Maybe it's an MCP server that needs to be configured or is already configured.\n\nI should check if Sorftime is a specific MCP server or product they're working with, and whether it's available as a global resource in their setup.\n","thinkingSignature":"dd1e0ac887f6602acefdb12469e4285a21806755ea40b5d8bce67646982733c8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你是问 Sorftime MCP 还是 SofaMCP？\n\n我现在搜不了网，信息有点断层。你说的 Sorftime 是：\n\n- **第三方 MCP 服务**（像 SofaMCP 那种，需要 key）\n- **还是你们自己搭的浏览器自动化服务**（你开头说跑通的那个）\n\n确认一下我好帮你配或者测。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3992,"output":391,"cacheRead":2