{"type":"message","id":"f0a9344d","parentId":"e37b1889","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:21:37.512Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if I can call/use \"Sorftime MCP\" or \"SofaMCP\". Let me check if there's an MCP server configured that I can use. I should look at the mcporter skill to understand how to call MCP tools, and check if there's a way to list available MCP tools.\n\nActually, I should try to use the mcporter skill or just try to call the MCP tool directly. But first, let me see what MCP tools are available to me.\n\nThe user seems to be asking if I can call the MCP tool directly. I don't have a specific MCP tool to call right now in my available tools. Let me check if there's a way to discover MCP servers or call their tools.\n\nActually, looking at my available tools, I don't see an MCP-specific tool except the `mcporter` skill which I should read to understand how to use it. But the user might be asking whether the MCP tool is already configured and callable.\n\nLet me try to see if there's an MCP tool available by checking if the mcporter skill can list tools.\n","thinkingSignature":"9f38c8150bcee08a3d1dc22440577ce1ef410539d66c9bb01b6b6cb1bd654393"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b3qo5ue4ez4s_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/mcporter/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":479,"output":257,"cacheRead":26752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27488,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778322087738,"responseId":"064e3da807af8be93a0de3dc28bf9a29"}}
{"type":"message","id":"eebd8554","parentId":"f0a9344d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:21:37.676Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b3qo5ue4ez4s_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: mcporter\ndescription: List, configure, authenticate, call, and inspect MCP servers/tools with mcporter over HTTP or stdio.\nhomepage: http://mcporter.dev\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"📦\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"mcporter\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"node\",\n              \"kind\": \"node\",\n              \"package\": \"mcporter\",\n              \"bins\": [\"mcporter\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install mcporter (node)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# mcporter\n\nUse `mcporter` to work with MCP servers directly.\n\nQuick start\n\n- `mcporter list`\n- `mcporter list <server> --schema`\n- `mcporter call <server.tool> key=value`\n\nCall tools\n\n- Selector: `mcporter call linear.list_issues team=ENG limit:5`\n- Function syntax: `mcporter call \"linear.create_issue(title: \\\"Bug\\\")\"`\n- Full URL: `mcporter call https://api.example.com/mcp.fetch url:https://example.com`\n- Stdio: `mcporter call --stdio \"bun run ./server.ts\" scrape url=https://example.com`\n- JSON payload: `mcporter call <server.tool> --args '{\"limit\":5}'`\n\nAuth + config\n\n- OAuth: `mcporter auth <server | url> [--reset]`\n- Config: `mcporter config list|get|add|remove|import|login|logout`\n\nDaemon\n\n- `mcporter daemon start|status|stop|restart`\n\nCodegen\n\n- CLI: `mcporter generate-cli --server <name>` or `--command <url>`\n- Inspect: `mcporter inspect-cli <path> [--json]`\n- TS: `mcporter emit-ts <server> --mode client|types`\n\nNotes\n\n- Config default: `./config/mcporter.json` (override with `--config`).\n- Prefer `--output json` for machine-readable results.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778322097675}}
