{"type":"message","id":"5e3d5cd9","parentId":"723e4038","timestamp":"2026-05-09T10:30:38.931Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the category report data. Let me try to add a record to the Feishu bitable. I need to figure out the structure.\n\nFrom the data I can see:\n- Category: Hair Clips & Hair Pins\n- Monthly sales: 391,523\n- Average price: $28,532.84 (this is in VND, not USD - 28,532 VND is about $1.15 USD)\n- Top 10 products with full details\n\nLet me write the top product to the bitable to test. I'll use the Feishu API directly to create a record.\n\nLooking at the fields:\n- 商品名称 (Product Name): \"Kẹp Chuối Lười Chuối Kẹp Tóc Tóc Đuôi Ngựa Cao Cố Định Hiện Vật Kẹp Dọc Phụ Kiện Tóc Cho Nữ-ALIA\"\n\n\n- 售价（本地货币）: 17000000 VND\n- 月销量: 10768\n- 站点: VN\n- 三级类目: Hair Clips & Hair Pins / 908552\n\nI need to convert the price properly. The report shows $17000.00, but that's in VND, not USD. Let me figure out the correct conversion - 17,000 VND is roughly $0.68 USD, so something seems off with how the price is being displayed in the report.\n\nLooking at the data more carefully, I'm seeing prices like \"$28532.84\" which doesn't make sense as USD for hair clips. These are definitely in VND. For the TOP1 product at 10768 VND, converting to USD gives around $0.43, which still feels too low. Let me verify the actual exchange rate - 1 USD ≈ 23,000 VND, so prices like 17000 VND would be under $1, which might actually be reasonable for budget hair accessories.\n\nThe bitable schema shows \"售价（本地货币）\" as a number field, so I should store the original VND price there rather than converting it. Now I need to decide whether to write individual records for each of the TOP50 products or aggregate them at the category level.\n\nLooking at what's needed for the SOP scoring system - monthly sales, average price, review counts, ratings - the category-level data covers most of these metrics. For individual products, I'd need to pull